---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5 flex justify-between items-center pr-2">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Resume</div>
    
    <!-- Download PDF Button -->
    <a href="/Ahmed_Zahran_Resume.pdf" download="Ahmed_Zahran_Resume.pdf" class="btn btn-outline btn-primary shrink-0">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 16v1a3 3 0 003 3h10a3 3 0 003-3v-1m-4-4l-4 4m0 0l-4-4m4 4V4" />
      </svg>
      Download PDF
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Emerging Cloud DevOps Engineer, certified as an AWS Solutions Architect and Cloud Practitioner, with a Bachelor's degree in Information Technology and hands-on expertise in cloud-native infrastructure[cite: 1]. Fluent in English (C1 level) and proficient in orchestrating scalable environments using Terraform, Kubernetes, and Docker[cite: 1]. Strong technical foundation in AWS serverless architectures, Linux system administration, and CI/CD automation[cite: 1]. Proven ability to engineer zero-trust deployment pipelines, implement Infrastructure as Code (IaC), and establish proactive observability to optimize and secure cloud operations[cite: 1].
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Cloud DevOps Intern"
      subtitle="iVolve"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 text-sm">
        <li><strong>Build & Containerization:</strong> Standardized application packaging using Gradle and Maven and engineered optimized multi-stage Dockerfiles to containerize Spring Boot, Node.js, and Python microservices[cite: 1].</li>
        <li><strong>Kubernetes Orchestration:</strong> Managed cluster resources and security by implementing RBAC, resource quotas, and node taints, while configuring persistent storage solutions and StatefulSets for database workloads[cite: 1].</li>
        <li><strong>Continuous Integration:</strong> Designed automated Jenkins pipelines to streamline the software delivery lifecycle, integrating unit testing, image scanning, and automated deployment stages[cite: 1].</li>
        <li><strong>GitOps Implementation:</strong> Deployed and configured ArgoCD to manage GitOps workflows, ensuring automated synchronization and consistency between Git repositories and Kubernetes cluster states[cite: 1].</li>
        <li><strong>Infrastructure Automation:</strong> Developed Ansible playbooks to automate server configuration and application deployment, utilizing Ansible Vault for secret management and dynamic inventory for AWS EC2 instance discovery[cite: 1].</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
    
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Cloud DevOps Engineer Scholarship"
      subtitle="National Telecommunication Institute (NTI)"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 text-sm">
        <li>Gained hands-on experience in network automation, cloud deployment, and infrastructure as code within an intensive DevOps training environment[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Automated configuration and management of Cisco, Juniper, and Arista network devices using Ansible playbooks, including VLAN provisioning and SNMP monitoring[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Deployed and managed containerized applications on Red Hat OpenShift using Helm and source-to-image workflows, handling cluster resources, nodes, and access controls[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Designed and executed automated infrastructure test cases using Robot Framework to validate network and system deployments[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Strengthened Linux system administration skills through practical work with Red Hat Linux, SELinux policies, firewalls, LVM, and file systems[cite: 1].</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Customer Service Agent"
      subtitle="TTEC & Concentrix – Cairo, Egypt"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 text-sm">
        <li>Managed 100+ daily customer inquiries in high-volume call center environments while consistently meeting service-level agreements (SLAs)[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Resolved technical and account-related issues efficiently under time pressure, demonstrating strong problem-solving and communication skills[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Documented workflows and tracked performance metrics, reinforcing attention to detail and process-oriented thinking applicable to DevOps operations[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Collaborated with cross-functional teams to meet operational targets, developing teamwork and reliability essential for production environments[cite: 1].</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Front-End Web Development"
      subtitle="Route Academy – Cairo, Egypt"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm">
        <li>Developed responsive web applications using React and JavaScript, consuming RESTful APIs to build dynamic user interfaces[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Implemented debugging, testing, and deployment practices, establishing a strong foundation for automation and CI/CD concepts[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Gained practical experience in version control and collaborative development workflows[cite: 1].</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Technical Projects</div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Cloud Resume Challenge (Serverless AWS Architecture & CI/CD)"
      subtitle="Personal Project"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm">
        <li>Engineered a zero-trust CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions and AWS OIDC, eliminating the reliance on long-lived static credentials for automated infrastructure deployments[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Codified cloud infrastructure (S3, Lambda, CloudFront) utilizing Terraform with remote state management, ensuring a highly available, version-controlled cloud architecture[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Enforced automated quality gates within the deployment pipeline, executing Python unit tests and Terraform syntax validation on every commit before production rollout[cite: 1].</li>
        <li>Implemented proactive observability by provisioning AWS CloudWatch metric alarms and SNS email notifications via IaC to monitor serverless compute health in real-time[cite: 1].</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor of Information Technology"
      subtitle="Faculty of Computers and Artificial Intelligence, Beni-suef, Egypt[cite: 1] | Graduation: 2022[cite: 1]"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate"
      subtitle="Issued June 2026 by Amazon Web Services (AWS)"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner"
      subtitle="Issued June 2026 by Amazon Web Services (AWS)"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-2 columns-1 mx-6 mb-10 text-sm">
    <li><strong>OS & Security:</strong> Linux Administration (Red Hat Admin I/II, SELinux, Firewalls, LVM)[cite: 1].</li>
    <li><strong>Automation & Scripting:</strong> Python, Ansible, Shell Scripting, Git[cite: 1].</li>
    <li><strong>Networking Foundations:</strong> VLANs, SNMP, Cisco[cite: 1].</li>
    <li><strong>Cloud & Orchestration:</strong> AWS (Core Services/Security), Terraform, Kubernetes, Docker, Red Hat OpenShift[cite: 1].</li>
    <li><strong>Development & APIs:</strong> REST/HTTPS APIs, React/JavaScript[cite: 1].</li>
    <li><strong>Languages & Communication:</strong> Arabic (Native), English (Fluent / C1)[cite: 1].</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>